\textbf{INSTRUCTIONS}
 

\index{Series}
 

Connecting components in \textit{series} means to connect them in-line with each other, so that there is but a single path for electrons to flow through them all.  If you connect batteries so that the positive of one connects to the negative of the other, you will find that their respective voltages add.  Measure the voltage across each battery individually as they are connected, then measure the total voltage across them both, like this:
 

 
