\end{itemize}
\index{Potentiometer}
 

Potentiometers are variable voltage dividers with a shaft or slide control for setting the division ratio.  They are manufactured in panel-mount as well as breadboard (printed-circuit board) mount versions.  Any style of potentiometer will suffice for this experiment.
 

\index{Potentiometer, linear vs. audio taper}
\index{Audio taper potentiometer}
\index{Linear taper potentiometer}
 

If you salvage a potentiometer from an old radio or other audio device, you will likely be getting what is called an \textit{audio taper} potentiometer.  These potentiometers exhibit a logarithmic relationship between division ratio and shaft position.  By contrast, a \textit{linear} potentiometer exhibits a direct correlation between shaft position and voltage division ratio.  I highly recommend a linear potentiometer for this experiment, and for most experiments in general.
 

