Try holding the wire in different positions next to a good, strong source of electric fields.  Try using a piece of aluminum foil clipped to the wire's end to maximize capacitance (and therefore its ability to intercept an electric field).  Try using different types of material to "shield" the wire from an electric field source.  What material(s) work best?  How does this compare with the AC \textit{magnetic} field experiment?
 

 

