\item Audio detector with headphones
\item 0.1 $\mu$F capacitor
\item One toggle switch, SPST ("Single-Pole, Single-Throw")
\end{itemize}
 

It is essential for this experiment that the low-voltage AC power supply be equipped with a center tap.  A transformer with a non-tapped secondary winding simply will not work for this circuit.
 

 

The diodes need not be exact model 1N4001 units.  Any of the "1N400X" series of rectifying diodes are suitable for the task, and they are quite easy to obtain.
 

\bigskip 
 

\textbf{CROSS-REFERENCES}
 

 

\textit{Lessons In Electric Circuits}, Volume 3, chapter 3: "Diodes and Rectifiers"
 

\bigskip 
 

\textbf{LEARNING OBJECTIVES}
 

\begin{itemize}
\item Design of a center-tap rectifier circuit
\item Measuring "ripple" voltage with a voltmeter
\end{itemize}
\bigskip 
 

