This circuit detects pulses of light striking the LED and converts them into relatively strong audio signals to be heard through the headphones.  Forrest Mims teaches that LEDs have the ability to \textit{produce} current when exposed to light, in a manner not unlike a semiconductor solar cell. \cite{MIM} By itself, the LED does not produce enough electrical power to drive the audio detector circuit, so a transistor is used to amplify the LED's signals.  If the LED is exposed to a pulsing source of light, a tone will be heard in the headphones.
 

 

