When this simulation is run through the SPICE program, it shows an input voltage of 5.937 volts and an output voltage of 5.095 volts, with an input current of 25.35 $\mu$A (2.535E-02 volts dropped across the 1 k$\Omega$ R$_{base}$ resistor).  Output current is, of course, 5.095 mA, inferred from the output voltage of 5.095 volts dropped across a load resistance of exactly 1 k$\Omega$.  You may change the "potentiometer" setting in this circuit by adjusting the values of R$_{pot1}$ and R$_{pot2}$, always keeping their sum at 10 k$\Omega$.
 


